Oluwatosin Omojuyigbe The Presidential Amnesty Programme on Tuesday hailed four of its beneficiaries on scholarship at the Afe Babalola University, Ado-Ekiti, for graduating with first class degrees. The Coordinator, PAP, Prof. Charles Dokubo, who noted that 19 other beneficiaries of the programme were also awarded second class degrees in various courses, added that 58 students sponsored by the amnesty programme graduated from the institution on Monday. In a statement, PAP explained that three of the first class degree awardees scored a minimum CGPA of 4.54 out of a possible 5.0 in the College of Engineering. They are, Porbeni Dakore (Electrical/Electronics Engineering); Tele Blessing (Mechanical Engineering); Roland Ebriyo (Electrical/Electronics Engineering); and Confidence Agu, who got first class degree in Medical Laboratory Science. Dokubo said, “The landmark achievement is due to the commitment of President Muhammadu Buhari towards deepening peace as a vehicle for development of the Niger Delta region.” Copyright PUNCH.
